<item>
            <title>[GROOVY-8948] BigDecimal to primitive conversion not working</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-8948</link>
                <project id="12318123" key="GROOVY">Groovy</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The following code will not compile with Groovy:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;Math&lt;/span&gt;.ceil(1/2)&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Groovy insists that it try to find Math.ceil(BigDecimal), as opposed to performing the conversion to a double.&#160; The following will work though:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;Math&lt;/span&gt;.ceil((&lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;double&lt;/span&gt;)1/2)&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;But the above should not be necessary as Groovy should unbox it.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Incidentally, this did work with version 2.4.12 and below.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
